{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the mathematics curriculum to be more relevant to real life",
        "additional_details": "I strongly believe that the government should change the curriculum as it is not setting people up for life outside of school. I don't think children should learn things that aren\u2019t going to help them in real life scenarios.",
        "background": "I would like the government to change the curriculum, so children can apply what they learn to their lives. I feel that currently, they are learning things that are not useful. I think children need to learn about real life maths e.g. mortgages, loans, debt and credit cards. ",
